s had any larger significance and i look back on that and say how on earth could we be so oblivious i guess it says something about that day and age that it didnt cross our minds p   a b c d the american abolish the sat by charles murray julyaugust  issue the american magazine july–august  archived from the original on january   retrieved january     narrowing the new class divide nytimescom retrieved march     deparle pp –  a b c upi qa with charles murray on human accomplishment by steve sailer october   istevecom october   retrieved january     charles murray shame project retrieved march     eric r wolf and joseph g jorgensen the new york review of books a special supplement anthropology on the warpath in thailand by eric r wolf and joseph g jorgensen november   new york review of books retrieved march     murray charles july    conversationswithbillkristolorg retrieved on   de parle   mcintosh  my epiphany came in thailand in the s when i first came to understand how badly bureaucracies dealt with human problems in the villages and how well with qualifications villagers dealt with their own problems given certain conditions gene expression  questions for charles murray  deparle p   cox catherine bly –  papers – a finding aid radcliffe college harvardedu january  retrieved september     nasa symposium on forty years of human spaceflight  the book was well reviewed rich densely packed and beautifully told filled with cliffhangers suspense and spinetingling adventure – charles sheffield washington post book world july   heartgripping so brilliantly told one can almost smell the perspiration in houston mission control charles petit san francisco chronicle july    quaker meeting the quaker economist  – the bell curve current location deparle p   two children from each marriage deparle pp –  murray charles  the curmudgeons guide to getting ahead  dos and donts of right behavior tough thinking clear writing and living a good life new york crown business isbn    doctor